  "summary": "Postinstall beacon exfiltrating host/process information",
  "details": "metrics-pipeline-d8k2 declares a postinstall lifecycle hook (\"postinstall\": \"node run.js\") that auto-executes on every install. The package ships beacon33.js and beacon_linux.js, which use child_process together with http/https to gather host identifiers (os.hostname(), os.platform(), process.platform) and process.env values and transmit them via outbound HTTP/HTTPS requests (http.get, http.request, POST). The package name pattern (random suffix), absence of any legitimate library functionality, and the presence of platform-specific beacon scripts wired to a postinstall trigger match the shape of an installer-targeted exfiltration dropper rather than a real metrics tool. Installing this package causes immediate, non-consensual collection and outbound transmission of installer environment data.",
